# Push to GitHub after edits

Whenever you change tracked files in this repository (HTML, CSS, JS, workflows, etc.), finish the task by:

1. `git add` the files you touched (or `git add -A` when the whole change set should ship).
2. `git commit` with a short, clear message describing what changed and why.
3. `git push origin main` (or the current branch if not `main`).

Do not leave fixes sitting only in the working tree unless the user explicitly asked not to push. If there is nothing to commit, say so and skip push.
